Package net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data Description

Data models for components live here. A data model provides a way to extract the data from the presentation. The data describes what should be displayed, the component describes how it should be displayed.

All models are defined by an interface. There are abstract implementations and concrete implementations of the data model interfaces. For simple models you may be able to use a concrete model instead of implementing your own. For example, when needing a tree model that will not contain a large number of nodes, the TreeNodeTreeModel and MutableTreeNodeImpl classes may be used.

Data models must fire events when the data changes. If you implement a model be sure to fire the appropriate events, otherwise the components may display incorrect data.

The TreeModelValidator class provides a way to test a TreeModel implementation to ensure it meets the contract of a TreeModel. If you have trouble with your tree model be sure to run the validation test.
